irs UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map  n      View Menu n       nDown arrow icon n n n n n n Down arrow icon Get Involved  Put yourself out there and get involved   There are tons of student leadership opportunities like the Residence Hall Association  PBMA  and Hall Council   n nGet Involved  n  n nGet Involved  n Hall Council Each residence hall has its own Hall Council  as well as plan programs for either educational or entertainment purposes  Anyone is eligible to join the Hall Council executive board  n      Join Hall Council  n     National Residence Hall Honorary  NRHH The National Residence Hall Honorary is representative of the top  % of student leaders in Campus Housing based on GPA and involvement  regional and national recognition to students making outstanding contributions to their residence halls  The three core values of NRHH are  Service  Leadership  and Recognition New Student Days New Student Days is a series of programs intended to welcome all incoming freshman and incoming transfer residents to campus and the city of Chicago  New Student Days is filled with many free and affordable on campus and off campus events designed to help freshman and transfers get acquainted with Chicago  but look forward to Chicago must  neighborhood visits  shows  and more   n      New Student Days n     Pathways to Black Male Achievement  PBMA PBMA is an engagement and retention organization that provides intentional programming and seeks to helps students explore what it means to be a Black male on a college campus  heritage  development and counteracting the negative images of Black males portrayed in the media  Everyone can participate in PBMA events regardless of ethnicity or gender  You can participate in many ways including attending events and programs  volunteering to help with events  joining the leadership team  and encouraging residents to participate Project LEAD Project LEAD is a three day program of workshops designed specifically to assist students in developing leadership skills and getting involved on campus from day one  This program allows first year and transfer students to move in early and get a head start adjusting to UIC and living on campus  n      Project LEAD n     Residence Hall Association  RHA RHA is a student organization for students who live on campus  RHA serves as a liaison between residents and Campus Housing staff  special events  leadership opportunities  and by providing a place to voice concerns about Campus Housing policy  procedure  and facilities  Any student who lives in the residence halls is automatically a member of RHA  Signature events  Sex in the Dark  Battle of the Residence Halls  Six Flags Fright Fest  Fall Ball  RHA Basketball Night  Ski trip  and trips to Broadway in Chicago shows SISTERS  Through strong sisterhood  participants of SISTERS explore Black identity  hegemonic norms  beauty standards and female empowerment  Everyone can participate in SISTERS events regardless of ethnicity or gender  all programs are open to everyone Work with Campus Housing Campus Housing offers a wide variety of student employment positions  but each position offers you another way to get involved with Campus Housing and grow as a leader  n      Student Staff Positions n     For more information about getting involved  contact Johnny Quintanilla  johnnyq uic edu johnnyq uic edu Join us at an upcoming Event  Pots and Shrubs Nappily Ever After GA  Earth Day Sit and Relax Laser Tag NRHH Chapter Meeting  Exec  Board Election NRHH Open Meeting  Balloon Popping GA  Beach Theme End of the Year Raffle General Body Meeting  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Campus Housing n         Future Apply           Rates Residence Halls Services Why Live on Campus Current Academic Support Apply Get Involved ReApp Services Affiliate Conference Housing Guest Housing Intern Housing Medical Students Button Menu About Housing Contact Us Dock MyContract Student Affairs Contact                           housing uic ed